sentences: Lee Tae-il (Hangul: 이태일, born September 24, 1990), better known by the mononym Taeil (Hangul: 태일), is a South Korean singer, signed under Seven Seasons.
In addition to his work with Block B, Taeil performed two solo concerts in Tokyo, Japan, on January 13, 2017.

In March 2018, Taeil was named as a judge for the Blind Musician singing competition, which is sponsored by the Korea Music Copyright Association, the Federation of Korean Music Performers, and the Korean Entertainment Producers' Association.
Taeil's first solo concert in Korea was announced November 2018 and scheduled to take place on December 22 and 23 in Seoul's Olympic Park K-Art Hall.
In April 2019, it was announced that Taeil and Park Kyung would hold two concerts in Seoul together on May 25 and 26.
After fulfilling his term of service, Taeil returned home on leave December 4, 2020, with his discharge becoming official the following month.
On June 10, Taeil announced that he would be entering into South Korea's compulsory military duty immediately.
